1
00:00:13,613 --> 00:00:14,637
永无止境的黑暗

2
00:00:14,714 --> 00:00:16,545
我们都很笨拙的人

3
00:00:16,616 --> 00:00:19,050
但我很勇敢，我很坚强

4
00:00:19,119 --> 00:00:21,553
不管谁来，只是闭上我的眼睛

5
00:00:21,621 --> 00:00:22,747
我不想听。不要说话。

6
00:00:22,822 --> 00:00:24,551
不要告诉我应该做什么

7
00:00:24,624 --> 00:00:27,058
Even though I'm brave

8
00:00:27,127 --> 00:00:29,755
I'm always alone, I know it already

9
00:00:29,829 --> 00:00:31,057
I'm already bruised

10
00:00:31,131 --> 00:00:32,564
Life's a jungle with no answers

11
00:00:32,632 --> 00:00:35,157
I'm lonely, sad and lost

12
00:00:35,235 --> 00:00:37,760
I'm trapped in here
This tiny grey building

13
00:00:37,837 --> 00:00:40,362
We're all trapped, floating in air

14
00:00:40,440 --> 00:00:41,873
Hear the car horn beep, beep

15
00:00:41,941 --> 00:00:43,772
We have nowhere to turn

16
00:00:43,843 --> 00:00:45,777
Can you help us?

17
00:00:45,845 --> 00:00:48,575
Who will trust us? We're trapped

18
00:00:48,648 --> 00:00:56,180
19 years old right now

19
00:00:56,256 --> 00:01:02,286
Nineteen

20
00:01:04,164 --> 00:01:05,188
Jeong-hun

21
00:01:05,265 --> 00:01:06,596
Min-seo

22
00:01:11,771 --> 00:01:13,705
Min-seo, what are you doing?

23
00:01:15,875 --> 00:01:20,505
What are you doing down there?
Always singing strange songs

24
00:01:21,381 --> 00:01:23,315
Aren't you going to school?

25
00:01:23,383 --> 00:01:27,114
School? No, I go to work today

26
00:01:30,290 --> 00:01:32,815
Skipping class for a measly casual job

27
00:01:33,993 --> 00:01:35,119
This is my seat

28
00:01:35,195 --> 00:01:37,925
Hey! I marked that page

29
00:01:37,997 --> 00:01:40,625
Don't study at the table
It ruins everyone's appetite

30
00:01:40,700 --> 00:01:42,133
I'm not the same as you

31
00:01:43,403 --> 00:01:44,233
How are we different?

32
00:01:44,304 --> 00:01:47,831
I go to a good university,
I'm going to be an accountant

33
00:01:47,907 --> 00:01:50,137
You go to a poor university
which you hardly ever attend

34
00:01:50,210 --> 00:01:52,542
- Not again!
- She's right

35
00:01:52,612 --> 00:01:53,738
Father...

36
00:01:53,813 --> 00:01:55,838
You need to think about the future

37
00:01:55,915 --> 00:01:57,246
I am thinking about the future

38
00:01:57,317 --> 00:02:00,548
- Not hard enough
- Watch it

39
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:03,145
You won't get a job with your degree

40
00:02:03,223 --> 00:02:06,158
You're already on your way
to becoming a failure

41
00:02:06,226 --> 00:02:10,856
You should study to acquire a license

42
00:02:11,231 --> 00:02:12,960
Hurry up and eat

43
00:02:13,032 --> 00:02:16,968
Yes, eat up so you can go
earn lots of money today

44
00:02:17,036 --> 00:02:18,367
Close your book

45
00:02:18,438 --> 00:02:19,871
- Hey!
- Watch your manners!

46
00:02:23,743 --> 00:02:24,971
I'm going

47
00:02:25,845 --> 00:02:29,576
Jeong-hun! Have breakfast!

48
00:02:33,253 --> 00:02:35,187
What's wrong with him...?

49
00:02:53,573 --> 00:02:54,505
Eun-a!

50
00:02:59,579 --> 00:03:00,511
Oh... hi

51
00:03:00,580 --> 00:03:04,311
You weren't answering my calls

52
00:03:04,884 --> 00:03:07,819
- Have you been ill?
- I'm fine

53
00:03:07,887 --> 00:03:11,323
You don't look good
You should see a doctor

54
00:03:11,391 --> 00:03:12,517
No, I'm fine

55
00:03:12,592 --> 00:03:16,824
Let's make sure, see a doctor

56
00:03:16,896 --> 00:03:18,523
I am seeing a doctor

57
00:03:24,704 --> 00:03:26,535
- Who's he?
- My boyfriend

58
00:03:27,106 --> 00:03:28,232
Boyfriend?

59
00:03:30,310 --> 00:03:32,039
I'm your boyfriend

60
00:03:32,111 --> 00:03:35,342
This is Su-bin, he's a med student

61
00:04:16,656 --> 00:04:18,988
- How are you feeling?
- I told you not to come

62
00:04:19,058 --> 00:04:23,392
- I finished early today
- They're so pretty, thanks

63
00:04:23,463 --> 00:04:24,987
I picked them from the garden

64
00:04:25,064 --> 00:04:28,295
- How's work going?
- Not bad

65
00:04:28,368 --> 00:04:29,494
I want to see

66
00:04:31,771 --> 00:04:33,705
The manager says I'm good

67
00:04:33,773 --> 00:04:36,708
She lets me help style customers too

68
00:04:36,776 --> 00:04:40,507
Did you design these hairstyles?

69
00:04:41,581 --> 00:04:45,312
- It's nothing
- They're good

70
00:04:46,185 --> 00:04:50,622
I don't need to worry about
you when I'm gone

71
00:04:50,690 --> 00:04:54,524
Don't say that.
You're going to get better

72
00:04:59,899 --> 00:05:03,027
- Hello?
- Where are you?

73
00:05:03,102 --> 00:05:06,538
Get down here now! We're busy!

74
00:05:07,607 --> 00:05:12,340
Sorry, but my mom's ill
I'm at the hospital

75
00:05:13,012 --> 00:05:14,843
Don't give me that excuse.

76
00:05:14,914 --> 00:05:16,939
You're old enough to look after yourself

77
00:05:17,016 --> 00:05:19,541
You're 19, an adult

78
00:05:19,619 --> 00:05:22,645
I pay you wages,
you should take responsibility

79
00:05:22,722 --> 00:05:26,351
Should I stay at work even
though my mother's dying?

80
00:05:26,426 --> 00:05:29,657
Are you shouting at me?

81
00:05:29,729 --> 00:05:31,356
I'm sorry, what I meant was...

82
00:05:31,431 --> 00:05:33,558
You're just an assistant

83
00:05:33,633 --> 00:05:36,761
Don't talk back to me like that

84
00:05:36,836 --> 00:05:38,861
I don't need you, you're fired!

85
00:05:38,938 --> 00:05:41,372
Hello? Hello?

86
00:05:55,254 --> 00:05:57,586
- Hello? I'm sorry about...
- Eun-yeong?

87
00:05:59,659 --> 00:06:04,392
- Yes, speaking...
- It's me...

88
00:06:05,965 --> 00:06:07,592
Are you feeling ill, Min-seo?

89
00:06:07,667 --> 00:06:08,099
I'm fine

90
00:06:08,167 --> 00:06:11,193
Should we go to dad's hospital?

91
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:12,202
No, I'm fine

92
00:06:12,271 --> 00:06:16,503
Have some cake then, I made it

93
00:06:16,576 --> 00:06:19,409
I ordered the butter from Switzerland

94
00:06:19,479 --> 00:06:20,411
You eat it, then

95
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:24,416
I made it for you, it's good for you

96
00:06:24,484 --> 00:06:27,009
You need to be strong to study

97
00:06:27,086 --> 00:06:30,419
Study hard, go to university next year

98
00:06:30,490 --> 00:06:32,424
- I'm going out
- Where are you going?

99
00:06:32,492 --> 00:06:33,516
The library

100
00:06:35,495 --> 00:06:37,827
I'm starting another day

101
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:43,734
Turning on the lights

102
00:06:45,004 --> 00:06:47,438
Who put that cup there?

103
00:06:48,107 --> 00:06:50,439
If I catch them, there'll be trouble

104
00:06:53,112 --> 00:06:54,545
You scared me!

105
00:06:54,614 --> 00:06:57,048
- Boss!
- You're here

106
00:06:57,116 --> 00:06:59,949
Could you help Yeong-ae clean up?

107
00:07:00,019 --> 00:07:03,147
Yeong-ae, take this with you

108
00:07:15,535 --> 00:07:18,163
- What's wrong with her?
- She said she's going to quit

109
00:07:18,237 --> 00:07:19,169
Why?

110
00:07:19,739 --> 00:07:23,175
She got a part in a film
wants to concentrate on her career

111
00:07:23,242 --> 00:07:26,575
I heard she went to acting school

112
00:07:26,646 --> 00:07:31,481
I paid her a high wage too
I guess she's not desperate

113
00:07:31,551 --> 00:07:36,488
You have me here
I'll stand by your side

114
00:07:36,956 --> 00:07:38,082
Thanks a lot

115
00:07:39,058 --> 00:07:42,994
Should I just give up school
and come here everyday?

116
00:07:44,063 --> 00:07:45,291
You're just being kind

117
00:07:45,364 --> 00:07:48,697
You're the kind one for
hiring a fool like me!

118
00:07:48,768 --> 00:07:52,898
I'm going to my son's school
I won't be back until lunch

119
00:07:52,972 --> 00:07:54,701
You're the man in charge

120
00:07:54,774 --> 00:07:55,502
Don't worry

121
00:07:57,777 --> 00:07:58,709
See you later

122
00:08:19,999 --> 00:08:21,830
You scared me

123
00:08:21,901 --> 00:08:24,529
- You're good
- At what? Sucking up?

124
00:08:24,604 --> 00:08:28,938
You sound like a real rapper
You're good

125
00:08:29,008 --> 00:08:30,134
It's nothing

126
00:08:30,209 --> 00:08:32,143
You should try out
for auditions

127
00:08:32,211 --> 00:08:33,838
You know, rap battles

128
00:08:33,913 --> 00:08:35,540
That's too difficult

129
00:08:35,615 --> 00:08:38,550
You have to make up
lyrics freestyle

130
00:08:38,618 --> 00:08:41,746
Just say what comes
to mind naturally

131
00:08:41,821 --> 00:08:44,551
The lyrics will be depressing then

132
00:08:44,624 --> 00:08:46,353
Why? Are you depressed?

133
00:08:46,425 --> 00:08:48,655
That's the story of my life

134
00:08:49,428 --> 00:08:52,261
Tell me about your life,
I'll listen

135
00:08:52,331 --> 00:08:54,561
I don't have anything to say

136
00:08:55,134 --> 00:08:58,865
You're so slow
I'm asking you out on a date

137
00:08:59,839 --> 00:09:00,669
You're what?

138
00:09:01,641 --> 00:09:03,666
Do I have to do all the work?

139
00:09:06,245 --> 00:09:08,679
I liked you from the beginning

140
00:09:09,749 --> 00:09:16,587
- No way Really?
- Why? I'm not your type?

141
00:09:16,656 --> 00:09:20,888
No, that's not it

142
00:09:22,161 --> 00:09:24,891
Girls like you always have boyfriends

143
00:09:24,964 --> 00:09:28,092
I don't date girls like that...
I don't even try

144
00:09:28,167 --> 00:09:31,000
I never imagined that a girl
like that would ask me out

145
00:09:31,070 --> 00:09:32,799
I don't talk to them because...

146
00:09:32,872 --> 00:09:35,306
What I mean is... I'm trying to say...

147
00:09:42,181 --> 00:09:45,014
I'm free... whenever you are

148
00:09:45,785 --> 00:09:47,616
Hang out with me after work?

149
00:09:49,088 --> 00:09:50,214
With you?

150
00:09:54,794 --> 00:09:56,125
I'm coming

151
00:09:57,697 --> 00:09:58,721
I'll get it

152
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:01,632
Hello.

153
00:10:02,902 --> 00:10:05,132
- It's $1 an hour, you can sit...
- I'm a member

154
00:10:06,906 --> 00:10:08,339
Pick any seat

155
00:10:47,446 --> 00:10:50,074
Hello. Are you a member?

156
00:10:50,149 --> 00:10:52,481
- I'm looking for someone
- Who?

157
00:10:52,551 --> 00:10:54,485
Is Yeong-ae here? I'm her friend

158
00:10:56,555 --> 00:10:58,887
Yeong-ae, your friend's here

159
00:11:03,462 --> 00:11:04,895
I don't care about your dreams

160
00:11:04,964 --> 00:11:06,192
Eun-yeong, please

161
00:11:06,265 --> 00:11:09,701
I came here to
make things clear

162
00:11:09,769 --> 00:11:12,294
I can't do it, I refuse to

163
00:11:13,773 --> 00:11:16,708
What gives you the right to ask me?

164
00:11:17,576 --> 00:11:20,409
I asked because you're my friend

165
00:11:20,479 --> 00:11:23,915
My answer's still no
Don't call me again

166
00:11:23,983 --> 00:11:25,211
Eun-yeong...

167
00:11:48,107 --> 00:11:54,945
- Hey... will you protect me?
- Of course I will I'll protect you

168
00:11:55,014 --> 00:11:59,747
- You will?
- I give you my word

169
00:12:16,836 --> 00:12:20,772
You have to watch over me. Promise me

170
00:12:32,852 --> 00:12:33,784
Follow me

171
00:12:38,958 --> 00:12:42,086
Who did it? Tell them to all come out

172
00:12:43,662 --> 00:12:44,890
I'll get them all!

173
00:12:53,572 --> 00:12:57,906
- Are we...
- What is it? Tell me

174
00:12:59,178 --> 00:13:03,808
Are we going to meet again?
Are we going out?

175
00:13:05,284 --> 00:13:06,512
I don't know

176
00:13:08,087 --> 00:13:09,816
Why not?

177
00:13:10,890 --> 00:13:15,224
How about if we
just live together?

178
00:13:16,395 --> 00:13:17,828
Live together?

179
00:13:18,397 --> 00:13:23,926
We're both 19... wouldn't it be fun?

180
00:13:27,106 --> 00:13:33,443
People don't think fondly of unmarried
couples living together

181
00:13:34,113 --> 00:13:38,345
My parents are really conservative

182
00:13:38,417 --> 00:13:40,351
I'm just kidding

183
00:13:47,026 --> 00:13:49,153
You're going to protect me, right?

184
00:14:29,168 --> 00:14:30,294
See you tomorrow!

185
00:14:49,788 --> 00:14:52,916
An adult, yet still a child

186
00:14:53,492 --> 00:14:55,926
Yearning for independence

187
00:14:56,495 --> 00:14:59,726
Endless opportunities

188
00:14:59,798 --> 00:15:05,532
An age of transition...
We were at that age, 19

189
00:15:10,309 --> 00:15:12,641
- Look!
- What?

190
00:15:14,013 --> 00:15:17,540
Her wallet's here...
she didn't get mugged

191
00:15:18,817 --> 00:15:21,445
You're right...what's this?

192
00:15:23,422 --> 00:15:26,949
She must have gone to a club

193
00:15:27,026 --> 00:15:27,958
A club??

194
00:15:28,027 --> 00:15:31,963
A nightclub that kids go to

195
00:15:33,032 --> 00:15:34,260
Where's her cell phone?

196
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:37,769
I don't see it. Maybe she dropped it

197
00:15:41,540 --> 00:15:43,565
Or someone threw it in the river

198
00:15:44,543 --> 00:15:47,774
We've got a smart one on our hands

199
00:15:52,051 --> 00:15:55,578
Mom! I don't have school today

200
00:15:55,654 --> 00:15:57,485
Where were you last night?

201
00:15:57,556 --> 00:16:00,389
Why do you care? Let me sleep

202
00:16:00,459 --> 00:16:02,984
- The police are here
- What?

203
00:16:04,463 --> 00:16:08,593
- Are you Seo Jeong-hun?
- Yes, why do you ask?

204
00:16:09,368 --> 00:16:11,996
- Do you know Oh Yeong-ae?
- Oh Yeong-ae?

205
00:16:13,372 --> 00:16:14,805
What's happened?

206
00:16:15,774 --> 00:16:18,800
Her body was found along the river

207
00:16:18,877 --> 00:16:20,003
What?

208
00:16:22,281 --> 00:16:23,407
You must be joking

209
00:16:24,083 --> 00:16:26,517
What does my son have to do with it?

210
00:16:27,386 --> 00:16:29,820
You'll need to come to the station

211
00:16:31,390 --> 00:16:36,623
Around 1:30 last night at the southern
end of the Han River

212
00:16:38,497 --> 00:16:41,728
A witness says they saw someone

213
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:44,030
push a young girl into the water

214
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:46,027
I don't believe it

215
00:16:46,805 --> 00:16:48,636
Who would do that to Yeong-ae?

216
00:16:50,109 --> 00:16:52,043
You worked together?

217
00:16:52,111 --> 00:16:57,048
Yes, it's been about 6 months

218
00:16:58,817 --> 00:17:01,047
- Were you close?
- Excuse me?

219
00:17:03,122 --> 00:17:06,057
I'm just asking if you were friends

220
00:17:06,125 --> 00:17:07,456
Were you?

221
00:17:07,526 --> 00:17:12,463
We chatted while working sometimes

222
00:17:14,233 --> 00:17:15,461
That's all

223
00:17:16,735 --> 00:17:17,861
Are you a student?

224
00:17:17,936 --> 00:17:21,372
I'm a freshman at Samhwa University

225
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:23,067
What's your major?

226
00:17:23,142 --> 00:17:24,666
Humanities and cultural studies

227
00:17:26,745 --> 00:17:28,076
What's that?

228
00:17:28,847 --> 00:17:34,683
The stylist attends to the customer
I help out and learn the ropes

229
00:17:34,753 --> 00:17:36,084
You're just a junior then

230
00:17:36,155 --> 00:17:37,679
We're referred to as staff

231
00:17:37,756 --> 00:17:39,189
Have you learnt a lot?

232
00:17:39,858 --> 00:17:41,485
- It doesn't matter now
- Why not?

233
00:17:41,560 --> 00:17:43,187
- I got fired
- When was that?

234
00:17:43,262 --> 00:17:44,786
- Yesterday
- Why did you get fired?

235
00:17:44,863 --> 00:17:48,196
I talked back to the boss
She fired me

236
00:17:48,267 --> 00:17:52,499
I would have done the same
So you were mad

237
00:17:52,571 --> 00:17:55,506
Your friend was murdered
yesterday too

238
00:17:55,574 --> 00:17:57,098
It's got nothing to do with me

239
00:17:57,176 --> 00:18:00,907
It's got nothing to do with you?
Isn't this camera yours?

240
00:18:02,281 --> 00:18:03,111
Is it yours?

241
00:18:03,182 --> 00:18:05,412
We went to a club, then...

242
00:18:05,484 --> 00:18:06,712
Where did you go afterwards?

243
00:18:08,987 --> 00:18:10,921
- Home
- Did you head straight home?

244
00:18:11,590 --> 00:18:16,118
You don't remember?
You can't think?

245
00:18:16,195 --> 00:18:18,823
No! I mean yes, no!

246
00:18:18,897 --> 00:18:20,831
We went to the river for some air

247
00:18:20,899 --> 00:18:22,423
You got some fresh air and...

248
00:18:24,503 --> 00:18:27,734
We just talked and went home early

249
00:18:28,707 --> 00:18:31,232
I mean it, we went home early

250
00:18:31,310 --> 00:18:32,743
You mean early in the morning...

251
00:18:34,213 --> 00:18:36,238
You don't know anything?

252
00:18:36,315 --> 00:18:38,840
Your friend died
but you know nothing

253
00:18:38,917 --> 00:18:41,545
- You're not even sad?
- It's unfortunate what happened

254
00:18:41,620 --> 00:18:45,147
She's a school mate
but we were never close

255
00:18:45,624 --> 00:18:48,149
She's not really my friend

256
00:18:49,628 --> 00:18:51,858
Is that why she called
you every day?

257
00:18:51,930 --> 00:18:54,763
Tell me who took
these photos then

258
00:18:54,833 --> 00:18:58,166
Your father's
a famous businessman

259
00:18:58,237 --> 00:19:02,173
You shouldn't get messed up like this

260
00:19:02,241 --> 00:19:05,472
Did you tell my parents?

261
00:19:07,045 --> 00:19:08,171
What?

262
00:19:08,247 --> 00:19:10,681
We looked at Yeong-ae's call records

263
00:19:10,749 --> 00:19:14,879
She called you last week 6 times in fact

264
00:19:15,954 --> 00:19:16,784
That's because...

265
00:19:16,855 --> 00:19:19,187
You're a precious son at home

266
00:19:19,758 --> 00:19:22,386
I've met mama boys
like you before

267
00:19:23,262 --> 00:19:26,493
