That's good... but do you think...

536
00:41:15,372 --> 00:41:17,203
It's fine, don't worry

537
00:41:19,176 --> 00:41:20,507
What I mean is...

538
00:41:22,179 --> 00:41:25,114
Mr. Park, I need to ask about your son

539
00:41:25,182 --> 00:41:29,016
You took him to the station...

540
00:41:29,787 --> 00:41:31,812
Did you have an arrest warrant?

541
00:41:35,292 --> 00:41:38,921
Taking someone without a warrant

542
00:41:38,996 --> 00:41:42,830
Questioning by force.
Isn't that illegal?

543
00:41:42,900 --> 00:41:43,832
That's right

544
00:41:43,901 --> 00:41:46,927
Conducting an investigation
without court consent...

545
00:41:47,004 --> 00:41:49,234
This is your son's camera

546
00:41:49,306 --> 00:41:53,743
He visited the internet cafe everyday

547
00:41:53,811 --> 00:41:56,245
He took photos of her in hiding

548
00:41:56,313 --> 00:41:57,541
Take a look for yourself

549
00:41:58,315 --> 00:42:01,546
- Your point being...?
- He was stalking her

550
00:42:03,320 --> 00:42:05,550
And that makes him a criminal?

551
00:42:05,623 --> 00:42:07,648
He ran while being investigated

552
00:42:07,725 --> 00:42:09,955
Of course we're suspicious of him

553
00:42:10,027 --> 00:42:11,551
Those photos...

554
00:42:11,629 --> 00:42:14,757
Do you have any proof
that my son took them?

555
00:42:34,652 --> 00:42:36,176
Jeong-hun!

556
00:42:36,954 --> 00:42:39,388
- Are you all right?
- Yes, I'm okay

557
00:42:39,456 --> 00:42:41,981
I heard you ran from the police

558
00:42:42,660 --> 00:42:44,287
They came to see me

559
00:42:44,361 --> 00:42:48,695
It just sort of happened...
but we're innocent

560
00:42:49,667 --> 00:42:52,795
We're going to stay on the run
until they find the real murderer

561
00:42:54,071 --> 00:42:55,299
Are they your friends?

562
00:42:58,075 --> 00:42:58,905
Boss

563
00:43:01,378 --> 00:43:05,405
- You believe me, right?
- Of course I believe you

564
00:43:05,482 --> 00:43:07,916
Yeong-ae and I weren't even close

565
00:43:07,985 --> 00:43:10,215
Why would I kill her?

566
00:43:11,188 --> 00:43:17,320
Yes... I know that. This is unfortunate

567
00:43:17,895 --> 00:43:21,422
It's not fair...
The police won't even listen

568
00:43:22,099 --> 00:43:25,933
It's just a case of bad luck

569
00:43:26,003 --> 00:43:29,837
The truth will be revealed

570
00:43:29,907 --> 00:43:33,741
- Don't worry about it
- Thank you

571
00:43:38,215 --> 00:43:41,241
It's not much

572
00:43:44,321 --> 00:43:45,447
How can I thank you?

573
00:43:45,522 --> 00:43:49,856
There's no need for that

574
00:43:50,728 --> 00:43:56,963
I should get back to Seoul
before the police visit again

575
00:43:57,034 --> 00:44:01,664
Take care of yourselves
Stay here tonight

576
00:44:01,739 --> 00:44:02,763
Thanks, boss

577
00:44:07,444 --> 00:44:08,968
Cheers!

578
00:44:11,749 --> 00:44:13,376
I needed a good drink

579
00:44:13,450 --> 00:44:15,384
You eat a lot for your size

580
00:44:17,454 --> 00:44:20,082
Now that we're full... what's next?

581
00:44:20,157 --> 00:44:23,684
We have no plans. Just go with the flow

582
00:44:23,761 --> 00:44:27,993
Let's stay here tonight, and tomorrow...

583
00:44:29,366 --> 00:44:30,492
What do we do tomorrow?

584
00:44:30,567 --> 00:44:32,398
It's not good to stay
in one place too long

585
00:44:32,469 --> 00:44:36,303
That's the first rule for runaways
Keep moving

586
00:44:36,373 --> 00:44:38,307
- Where should we go?
- How about the beach?

587
00:44:38,375 --> 00:44:40,502
Good idea! I haven't been in ages

588
00:44:40,577 --> 00:44:43,307
- I've never been
- You're joking!

589
00:44:43,380 --> 00:44:44,904
- I'm not
- Are you Mongolian?

590
00:44:44,982 --> 00:44:48,418
All Koreans have been to
the beach at least once

591
00:44:50,387 --> 00:44:55,120
You both think everyone's like you

592
00:44:56,293 --> 00:45:01,026
Never been to the beach
Never owned an MP3 player

593
00:45:01,098 --> 00:45:03,931
Can't even eat 3 meals a day
There are a lot of kids like that

594
00:45:06,103 --> 00:45:08,833
You can't even imagine it, right?

595
00:45:11,408 --> 00:45:13,239
Let's go to the beach then

596
00:45:14,611 --> 00:45:17,045
What else? What do you want to do?

597
00:45:20,417 --> 00:45:26,253
Go to sea, get on a boat...
Pose like the scene in 'Titanic'

598
00:45:27,024 --> 00:45:30,357
I have no thoughts about my life

599
00:45:30,427 --> 00:45:34,261
You must have plans for the future

600
00:45:34,832 --> 00:45:36,265
I have no plans at all

601
00:45:36,333 --> 00:45:39,860
You're only 19. You have no dreams?

602
00:45:39,937 --> 00:45:47,275
Dreams...? I don't know
Number 13, do you?

603
00:45:48,545 --> 00:45:51,173
I have so many plans

604
00:45:51,248 --> 00:45:54,081
English at 10am, math at 12:30pm

605
00:45:54,151 --> 00:45:57,086
then TOEFL in the evening
University,

606
00:45:57,154 --> 00:46:01,591
study abroad then get my MBA and...

607
00:46:02,960 --> 00:46:03,984
You're giving me a headache

608
00:46:04,061 --> 00:46:06,188
Tell us what your dreams are

609
00:46:06,263 --> 00:46:09,994
Well... I want to go to sea

610
00:46:10,067 --> 00:46:12,399
You haven't been to sea as well?
You haven't been on a boat?

611
00:46:12,469 --> 00:46:16,098
I've been on a cruise, on a big ship

612
00:46:16,173 --> 00:46:17,902
Then why do you want to go to sea?

613
00:46:18,575 --> 00:46:19,599
To go fishing?

614
00:46:20,577 --> 00:46:21,908
No I want to...

615
00:46:24,681 --> 00:46:25,511
Do this too

616
00:46:31,488 --> 00:46:37,324
Hey! Number 13! You're naughty!

617
00:46:37,394 --> 00:46:40,022
What about it? I don't get it

618
00:46:44,301 --> 00:46:45,131
What is it?

619
00:47:11,228 --> 00:47:15,255
- It's a rap battle!
- They're all pretty good

620
00:47:23,340 --> 00:47:26,571
Okay, stop there How was it?
Did you enjoy it?

621
00:47:26,643 --> 00:47:27,575
Yes!

622
00:47:27,644 --> 00:47:29,874
- Are you all having fun?
- Yes!

623
00:47:32,349 --> 00:47:34,283
Who will be our winner?

624
00:47:34,351 --> 00:47:36,979
If you liked this person, clap now!

625
00:47:39,656 --> 00:47:41,886
Should I call for back-up?

626
00:47:42,459 --> 00:47:44,689
Why don't we just bring in a SWAT
team to take out 3 kids?

627
00:47:50,767 --> 00:47:53,895
$1,000 is up for grabs!

628
00:47:58,976 --> 00:48:00,603
You rapped before, you're good

629
00:48:00,677 --> 00:48:02,508
I'm not good

630
00:48:04,081 --> 00:48:05,912
Here! My friend's going!

631
00:48:05,983 --> 00:48:07,211
We have a challenger,

632
00:48:07,284 --> 00:48:09,912
- give him a clap
- Hurry up, go

633
00:48:10,988 --> 00:48:12,319
Come on out!

634
00:48:24,001 --> 00:48:28,028
Go back study, get out of here

635
00:48:28,105 --> 00:48:30,733
Go to your parents, ask for money

636
00:48:31,008 --> 00:48:34,341
Get out, get out yeah

637
00:48:34,411 --> 00:48:40,350
come on~ come on~

638
00:48:44,621 --> 00:48:46,953
Close your mouth, watch your words

639
00:48:47,024 --> 00:48:49,652
You stand here but you're nothing

640
00:48:49,726 --> 00:48:52,354
Listen up, listen carefully

641
00:48:52,429 --> 00:48:55,159
You rap just like a broken car

642
00:48:55,232 --> 00:48:57,462
Listen up, listen to my rap

643
00:48:57,534 --> 00:49:01,163
I don't know you, your broken dreams

644
00:49:01,238 --> 00:49:07,177
I don't know where I'm headed

645
00:49:07,244 --> 00:49:11,180
Don't think you know me, you don't

646
00:49:11,248 --> 00:49:16,982
Look at your expressions now

647
00:49:21,558 --> 00:49:24,186
Big Bang, I've got what it takes

648
00:49:24,261 --> 00:49:27,287
This mic, this stage is all mine

649
00:49:27,364 --> 00:49:29,798
Don't make fun of me, it's not new

650
00:49:29,866 --> 00:49:32,494
Try to make me cry if you can

651
00:49:32,569 --> 00:49:35,197
Come on, is this the best you can do?

652
00:49:35,272 --> 00:49:37,797
You'll regret having challenged me

653
00:49:37,874 --> 00:49:40,809
Everybody tries to imitate me

654
00:49:40,877 --> 00:49:43,402
I'm upset, I'm unhappy, bang bang

655
00:49:43,480 --> 00:49:48,213
Worship my brother, my parents...

656
00:49:54,391 --> 00:49:55,415
Why did he stop?

657
00:49:57,594 --> 00:49:59,027
It's them!

658
00:50:03,200 --> 00:50:05,327
- Isn't that them?
- I think you're right

659
00:50:05,402 --> 00:50:06,835
- Let's go!
- Hurry up, go

660
00:50:36,433 --> 00:50:38,162
How long will you keep running?

661
00:50:39,136 --> 00:50:41,661
If you're innocent, come out!
Come out and tell us

662
00:50:42,839 --> 00:50:45,672
What happened the day Yeong-ae died

663
00:50:46,543 --> 00:50:49,068
Tell me why you took photos of her

664
00:50:49,146 --> 00:50:51,080
Why did you stalk her?

665
00:50:52,749 --> 00:50:53,875
Listen up

666
00:50:55,552 --> 00:51:02,185
I'm going to get you kids
I don't care what it takes

667
00:51:15,472 --> 00:51:16,598
Tell us the truth

668
00:51:20,477 --> 00:51:23,503
About Yeong-ae's photos, stalking her

669
00:51:25,282 --> 00:51:26,909
He was talking to you

670
00:51:29,386 --> 00:51:30,512
Tell us

671
00:51:31,888 --> 00:51:34,914
Don't talk like that... you're not a cop

672
00:51:38,195 --> 00:51:39,526
I'm sorry.

673
00:51:40,197 --> 00:51:41,926
What are you sorry about?

674
00:51:42,499 --> 00:51:46,833
The truth is... I watched her secretly

675
00:51:47,804 --> 00:51:51,331
- Why would you do that?
- She was so pretty...

676
00:51:51,408 --> 00:51:55,435
but I couldn't talk to her

677
00:51:55,512 --> 00:51:57,343
I didn't mean any harm

678
00:51:57,414 --> 00:51:59,746
What you did is harmful

679
00:51:59,816 --> 00:52:01,340
That's what stalkers and perverts do

680
00:52:01,418 --> 00:52:03,750
Don't be so harsh on him

681
00:52:03,820 --> 00:52:05,151
Aren't you angry?

682
00:52:06,223 --> 00:52:07,656
He's been lying all this time

683
00:52:07,724 --> 00:52:10,158
She's got nothing to do with me

684
00:52:10,227 --> 00:52:11,353
I don't even remember her face

685
00:52:11,428 --> 00:52:14,261
You don't remember her face?

686
00:52:17,334 --> 00:52:18,858
I actually believed you

687
00:52:19,636 --> 00:52:21,968
- I'm sorry
- Stop pretending

688
00:52:22,038 --> 00:52:25,269
Acting helpless, as though
you know nothing

689
00:52:25,342 --> 00:52:28,175
- What I mean is...
- Don't say anything

690
00:52:28,245 --> 00:52:32,272
I can't trust you. Did you kill her?

691
00:52:32,349 --> 00:52:35,477
- What?
- Stop it, that's enough

692
00:53:22,899 --> 00:53:25,834
Are you all right? Where are you now?

693
00:53:28,805 --> 00:53:32,536
We're fine, heading towards Sokcho

694
00:53:38,114 --> 00:53:41,345
Am I doing the right thing?

695
00:53:42,018 --> 00:53:44,248
You should cooperate with the police

696
00:53:44,321 --> 00:53:47,347
Please promise me one thing

697
00:53:47,424 --> 00:53:48,755
What is it?

698
00:53:48,825 --> 00:53:53,558
They may be criminals,
but they're good kids

699
00:53:53,630 --> 00:53:56,861
Please don't harm them

700
00:53:58,335 --> 00:53:59,962
Don't worry about that

701
00:54:02,339 --> 00:54:03,271
Let's go

702
00:54:03,340 --> 00:54:04,773
Good bye

703
00:54:07,143 --> 00:54:10,772
I've divided the money up evenly

704
00:54:14,951 --> 00:54:16,475
Let's split up now

705
00:54:17,454 --> 00:54:21,288
- Do we have to?
- Yes, I've had enough

706
00:54:21,358 --> 00:54:23,883
You wanted to run away together

707
00:54:23,960 --> 00:54:26,485
I changed my mind, I'll travel alone

708
00:54:26,563 --> 00:54:28,394
We're not going on a boat?

709
00:54:29,366 --> 00:54:31,300
Why don't the 2 of you go?

710
00:54:31,368 --> 00:54:32,995
You look good together anyway

711
00:54:33,670 --> 00:54:35,297
What are you going on about?

712
00:54:36,873 --> 00:54:38,898
I don't know your names,

713
00:54:38,975 --> 00:54:40,909
I'll probably never see you again

714
00:54:40,977 --> 00:54:41,807
Have a good life then

715
00:54:49,786 --> 00:54:50,810
He's so stupid

716
00:54:53,590 --> 00:54:54,818
I'm sorry

717
00:54:55,792 --> 00:54:57,521
Stop saying you're sorry

718
00:54:57,594 --> 00:54:59,926
I should have told the truth

719
00:55:00,697 --> 00:55:05,031
I didn't think you would believe me

720
00:55:06,503 --> 00:55:09,336
- I'm really sorry
- Stop saying that!

721
00:55:09,406 --> 00:55:11,033
I'm sorry, I'm sorry...

722
00:55:11,107 --> 00:55:12,631
How many times have you said that?

723
00:55:13,410 --> 00:55:17,744
Sorry Oh, sorry... oops

724
00:55:19,416 --> 00:55:20,440
I'm going too

725
00:55:21,918 --> 00:55:23,647
A girl I know died

726
00:55:23,720 --> 00:55:26,553
I've been mucking around like this

727
00:55:26,623 --> 00:55:28,352
I wasn't thinking straight

728
00:55:29,926 --> 00:55:30,756
I'm going

729
00:56:09,666 --> 00:56:10,997
I am thinking about the future

730
00:56:11,067 --> 00:56:12,796
Not hard enough

731
00:56:12,869 --> 00:56:15,497
You've started on the path to failure

732
00:56:15,572 --> 00:56:18,598
Find a way to make up for it

733
00:56:19,175 --> 00:56:22,906
They pay to send you to
school and you skip classes

734
00:56:22,979 --> 00:56:26,415
You go to clubs, hook up with girls

735
00:56:26,483 --> 00:56:27,609
How old are you?

736
00:56:50,607 --> 00:56:53,940
Is something wrong? Tell me!

737
00:56:55,912 --> 00:57:00,042
I'm asking you out on a date
I liked you from the beginning

738
00:57:01,818 --> 00:57:03,547
You have to protect me...

739
00:57:04,521 --> 00:57:05,453
promise

740
00:57:09,225 --> 00:57:11,250
You promised to protect me

741
00:57:44,661 --> 00:57:46,788
You didn't come with your parents?

742
00:57:47,363 --> 00:57:48,193
No.

743
00:57:50,767 --> 00:57:53,099
Please don't tell them I came

744
00:57:53,169 --> 00:57:54,796
As you wish

745
00:58:24,200 --> 00:58:26,634
Hello? Hello?

746
00:58:27,203 --> 00:58:31,833
It's you! Min-seo! Are you all right?

747
00:58:32,809 --> 00:58:34,333
Where are you now?

748
00:58:35,712 --> 00:58:39,546
- Are you hurt?
- I'm fine, Mom

749
00:58:40,416 --> 00:58:43,749
Is father angry with me?

750
00:58:44,721 --> 00:58:50,751
He's worried sick about you...
Are you sure you're not hurt?

751
00:58:52,428 --> 00:58:56,558
Listen to me carefully

752
00:58:57,033 --> 00:59:01,561
You can't come home,
don't even come near here

753
00:59:01,638 --> 00:59:05,574
If the press finds out,
it will be a huge mess

754
00:59:05,642 --> 00:59:09,578
Our lawyer will handle things
You just do as you're told

755
00:59:09,646 --> 00:59:11,375
Let me speak to him

756
00:59:11,447 --> 00:59:15,975
He'll call you soon, hang up now

757
00:59:16,052 --> 00:59:18,577
Don't hang up, let me speak...

758
00:59:19,856 --> 00:59:21,380
Do you understand me?

759
00:59:21,457 --> 00:59:25,393
- Give me the phone
- Stay out of this

760
00:59:25,461 --> 00:59:26,587
Hello...?

761
00:59:36,973 --> 00:59:42,411
You're busy, don't worry about me

762
00:59:43,880 --> 00:59:47,714
Working on the weekends,
I hope they're paying you well

763
00:59:47,784 --> 00:59:52,619
Everyone wants me to do their hair

764
00:59:54,390 --> 00:59:55,823
Your daughter?

765
00:59:55,892 --> 01:00:00,226
It's all right... I'm eating well

766
01:00:01,297 --> 01:00:06,428
I even ate a whole banana yesterday

767
01:00:07,804 --> 01:00:11,240
Don't worry about me, work hard

768
01:00:12,909 --> 01:00:14,137
Thanks mom

769
01:00:17,513 --> 01:00:22,951
I'll visit soon and bring you treats

770
01:00:25,421 --> 01:00:28,948
Sorry, I have to go now

771
01:00:58,254 --> 01:01:03,385
- Hello...mom? Hello?
- Come in number 13, over

772
01:01:04,761 --> 01:01:08,697
Number 1 ! where are you?
What are you doing?

773
01:01:09,265 --> 01:01:11,699
I came out to the beach for a walk

774
01:01:12,268 --> 01:01:16,204
In my pocket... I found your MP3 player

775
01:01:17,173 --> 01:01:20,802
I don't want you to report me as a thief

776
01:01:20,877 --> 01:01:22,105
Come get your stuff

777
01:01:25,081 --> 01:01:27,311
Here? The beach...

778
01:01:30,086 --> 01:01:31,713
I don't really know where

779
01:01:32,588 --> 01:01:34,112
Tell me where you are

780
01:02:13,830 --> 01:02:14,558
Hurry up!

781
01:02:24,240 --> 01:02:26,970
We're fugitives now

782
01:02:27,043 --> 01:02:28,874
It's dangerous sitting out like that

783
01:02:28,945 --> 01:02:29,775
I'm sorry

784
01:02:30,546 --> 01:02:33,071
- Here, it's yours
- Thank you

785
01:02:33,149 --> 01:02:33,877
It's all right

786
01:02:36,252 --> 01:02:39,187
Where's number 2? In her room?

787
01:02:40,656 --> 01:02:44,490
Were you... in the same room?

788
01:02:46,863 --> 01:02:49,297
We split up just after you left

789
01:02:49,365 --> 01:02:52,596
Why? You like her

790
01:02:53,669 --> 01:02:57,503
What..? I don't like her

791
01:02:57,573 --> 01:02:59,803
I left you alone on purpose

792
01:03:00,676 --> 01:03:02,007
I mean it

793
01:03:02,879 --> 01:03:04,403
You're the one who likes her

794
01:03:04,480 --> 01:03:05,310
Me?

795
01:03:06,482 --> 01:03:08,814
Me? Like her?

796
01:03:10,486 --> 01:03:11,510
Don't say that!

797
01:03:13,089 --> 01:03:14,420
She's not even a girl

798
01:03:15,391 --> 01:03:17,916
She's not my type, you can have her

799
01:03:19,195 --> 01:03:20,822
She's not my type either

800
01:03:28,204 --> 01:03:29,933
I think she hurt her ankle

801
01:03:31,007 --> 01:03:35,137
She sprained it last night
It was swollen this morning

802
01:03:36,412 --> 01:03:38,642
She was limping around before

803
01:03:41,417 --> 01:03:42,850
Do you know where she is?

804
01:03:43,519 --> 01:03:45,646
I think she'll still be around

805
01:03:46,622 --> 01:03:49,352
Probably, her ankle's sore...

806
01:04:07,343 --> 01:04:08,469
Let me go!

807
01:04:11,948 --> 01:04:13,882
Don't touch me!

808
01:04:15,351 --> 01:04:16,477
It's her!

809
01:04:22,258 --> 01:04:23,384
Let me go!

810
01:05:56,052 --> 01:05:57,986
How about a glass of soju?

811
01:05:58,054 --> 01:05:59,385
We're on duty

812
01:06:12,168 --> 01:06:16,195
Your necklace... isn't it for women?

813
01:06:19,175 --> 01:06:21,700
You must have strange taste

814
01:06:22,278 --> 01:06:25,213
It belonged to my wife

815
01:06:28,684 --> 01:06:30,515
I proposed to her with this

816
01:06:31,887 --> 01:06:35,823
I never bought her a proper gift

817
01:06:38,094 --> 01:06:42,622
Your wife was beaten by teenagers...

818
01:06:47,803 --> 01:06:50,738
Do you think it's silly that I'm
chasing after those kids?

819
01:06:50,806 --> 01:06:52,137
Of course not

820
01:06:52,208 --> 01:06:54,335
You probably think I'm trying
to get my revenge

821
01:06:54,410 --> 01:06:55,741
I don't think that

822
01:06:56,412 --> 01:06:58,744
- Don't lie to me
- I'm not

823
01:07:00,116 --> 01:07:02,141
- Have you finished?
- Yes

824
01:07:03,719 --> 01:07:05,050
It's a small town.

825
01:07:05,121 --> 01:07:09,455
We'll find them in internet cafes,
saunas in no time

826
01:07:09,525 --> 01:07:13,052
We're going to search
for them all night?

827
01:07:13,129 --> 01:07:15,256
We're not here to relax at the beach

828
01:07:19,435 --> 01:07:21,665
The stars look like they'll fall down

829
01:07:22,338 --> 01:07:26,172
They feel so much closer than in Seoul

830
01:07:27,443 --> 01:07:30,378
I wanted to be an astronomer
when I was young

831
01:07:30,446 --> 01:07:32,073
I wanted to be an astronaut

832
01:07:33,149 --> 01:07:39,384
We had a lot of dreams
when we were young, right?

833
01:07:39,455 --> 01:07:43,084
I used to look at the stars more often

834
01:07:45,161 --> 01:07:49,291
Sky, universe, stars

835
01:07:49,365 --> 01:07:54,098
Sea, wind, trees, grass

836
01:07:55,171 --> 01:07:57,901
What are you doing? What's he up to?

837
01:07:57,973 --> 01:07:59,702
Leave him, he's listening to music...

838
01:07:59,775 --> 01:08:02,801
Look! Did you see it?

839
01:08:02,878 --> 01:08:05,904
Sure... a shooting star

840
01:08:05,981 --> 01:08:09,314
Number 13, did you see?
What are you doing?

841
01:08:09,385 --> 01:08:11,114
- What are you listening to?
- Why? what happened?

842
01:08:11,187 --> 01:08:13,121
A shooting star. You didn't see it?

843
01:08:13,189 --> 01:08:15,316
What are you listening to?

844
01:08:15,991 --> 01:08:18,425
- It's a song I made
- You wrote it?

845
01:08:18,494 --> 01:08:20,621
You write songs? Let me listen

846
01:08:20,696 --> 01:08:22,630
You're such a mystery

847
01:08:22,698 --> 01:08:24,825
I can't hear... what is it?

848
01:08:24,900 --> 01:08:26,834
It's just the instrumental track

849
01:08:26,902 --> 01:08:29,530
- Sing it for us
- Let's listen to it live

850
01:08:29,605 --> 01:08:32,335
- It's not very good
- Come on, let us hear it

851
01:08:32,408 --> 01:08:35,741
- It's not finished yet
- Sing it! Please?

852
01:08:44,620 --> 01:08:51,458
Are you all right, is everything okay

853
01:08:51,527 --> 01:08:58,160
You left without a trace...

854
01:08:58,234 --> 01:09:04,173
to another world

855
01:09:06,942 --> 01:09:13,177
After time passes and I'm born again

856
01:09:13,249 --> 01:09:19,779
I'll tell you that I love you first

857
01:09:19,855 --> 01:09:25,293
All the things I wanted to say

858
01:09:25,361 --> 01:09:34,599
I'll confess my love to you

859
01:09:34,670 --> 01:09:41,200
The one person that I've loved

860
01:09:41,277 --> 01:09:47,512
If we're able to meet tomorrow

861
01:09:47,583 --> 01:09:53,317
Greet me with a smile

862
01:09:53,389 --> 01:09:59,521
Tell me you've been well

863
01:09:59,595 --> 01:10:06,228
You're the only one for me

864
01:10:06,302 --> 01:10:11,638
I miss you so much

865
01:10:11,707 --> 01:10:14,835
I'm brave enough to tell you now

866
01:10:14,910 --> 01:10:20,246
I've always wanted to say this

867
01:10:20,316 --> 01:10:26,653
I love you

868
01:10:36,832 --> 01:10:38,356
We had a bad run

869
01:10:39,435 --> 01:10:42,563
Nothing serious, but she's hurt

870
01:10:44,840 --> 01:10:47,570
It's not broken, but it hurts

871
01:10:49,645 --> 01:10:52,773
Sure. An X-ray would help

872
01:10:53,549 --> 01:11:00,478
I don't think I can go there...
I'll send someone else

873
01:11:00,556 --> 01:11:02,888
Can you tell me where you are?

874
01:11:03,659 --> 01:11:04,887
Let me get a pen

875
01:11:08,864 --> 01:11:10,593
You're at a temple

876
01:11:12,067 --> 01:11:15,002
I know where it is

877
01:11:29,084 --> 01:11:31,518
Sorry to interrupt you both

878
01:11:31,587 --> 01:11:32,918
Don't overreact.

879
01:11:32,988 --> 01:11:35,718
He was tying his handkerchief
around my ankle

880
01:11:36,392 --> 01:11:40,522
You carry a handkerchief?
You're so weird

881
01:11:42,698 --> 01:11:43,630
Here, for your ankle

882
01:11:50,406 --> 01:11:51,532
I could do it myself

883
01:11:51,607 --> 01:11:55,338
Just say thanks, be cute
Guys like cute girls

884
01:11:55,411 --> 01:11:57,345
I know I'm not cute

885
01:11:58,213 --> 01:12:03,150
- No, you're really cute
- Don't say that out of pity

886
01:12:03,218 --> 01:12:04,048
I mean it

887
01:12:04,119 --> 01:12:07,953
Look at you throwing
pick-up lines at her

888
01:12:08,023 --> 01:12:11,652
Give me your handkerchief again

889
01:12:13,929 --> 01:12:15,760
I put a patch on it for you

890
01:12:15,831 --> 01:12:17,560
The yellow looks ugly,

891
01:12:17,633 --> 01:12:19,760
plus it won't fall off with
the handkerchief over it

892
01:12:19,835 --> 01:12:22,360
You're going to cover my ugly
patch with his handkerchief?

893
01:12:22,438 --> 01:12:24,770
Stop it Give it to me then

894
01:12:28,243 --> 01:12:29,471
What's this?

895
01:12:30,045 --> 01:12:32,878
- The work of a stalker?
- Give it to me

896
01:12:33,549 --> 01:12:34,982
Don't look at them

897
01:12:36,051 --> 01:12:40,784
- It's Yeong-ae
- Let me see...it is her

898
01:12:42,057 --> 01:12:43,888
I'm not a pervert

899
01:12:43,959 --> 01:12:45,392
The photos turned out nice

900
01:12:45,461 --> 01:12:48,589
I was going to give them to her later

901
01:12:50,165 --> 01:12:51,189
I feel sorry for her

902
01:12:55,471 --> 01:12:59,805
Actually... I've been hiding something

903
01:13:02,578 --> 01:13:07,106
I said I didn't know
why she needed money

904
01:13:09,685 --> 01:13:12,813
She told me when we met

905
01:13:13,489 --> 01:13:17,118
I need money to attend acting school

906
01:13:17,793 --> 01:13:21,627
I told him I wanted to break up
after I got the part

907
01:13:21,697 --> 01:13:25,428
He told me to pay back every cent

908
01:13:25,501 --> 01:13:29,528
Or he'll tell everyone about us

909
01:13:29,605 --> 01:13:31,436
Don't ask me for money

910
01:13:31,507 --> 01:13:33,532
It's your problem, you handle it

911
01:13:33,609 --> 01:13:36,237
I wouldn't ask unless I was desperate

912
01:13:36,311 --> 01:13:40,145
Please help me This is
going to be my big break

913
01:13:40,215 --> 01:13:42,945
It's my dream! I want to achieve it

914
01:13:43,018 --> 01:13:45,043
They're your dreams, not mine

915
01:13:46,622 --> 01:13:47,953
Eun-yeong, please

916
01:13:50,125 --> 01:13:53,253
I shouldn't have been so cold

917
01:13:54,630 --> 01:13:58,464
It's not your fault
Don't blame yourself

918
01:14:05,140 --> 01:14:07,665
Wait... look at this

919
01:14:09,845 --> 01:14:11,278
I think it's him

920
01:14:11,847 --> 01:14:15,078
Isn't this your boss?

921
01:14:16,251 --> 01:14:17,183
What did you say?

922
01:14:17,252 --> 01:14:21,279
- Look at this photo
- Show me... it is him!

923
01:14:21,957 --> 01:14:23,288
I didn't notice before

924
01:14:23,358 --> 01:14:26,486
but he's behind her in
all of these photos

925
01:14:27,062 --> 01:14:28,996
That is his car

926
01:14:29,865 --> 01:14:31,492
Why would she get in his car?

927
01:14:32,968 --> 01:14:33,900
Hang on...

928
01:14:34,570 --> 01:14:36,094
He's married

929
01:14:36,171 --> 01:14:38,503
Then the man you
said Yeong-ae...

930
01:14:38,574 --> 01:14:41,202
The married guy!
It can't be...

931
01:14:43,178 --> 01:14:44,611
I just talked to him
on the phone

932
01:14:46,882 --> 01:14:49,009
After he came to the resort...

933
01:14:49,084 --> 01:14:52,212
Right! The detectives came then!

934
01:14:53,088 --> 01:14:54,919
How would they have known unless...

935
01:14:54,990 --> 01:14:57,515
My boss isn't like that!

936
01:15:30,425 --> 01:15:33,053
They were here until just now

937
01:15:33,128 --> 01:15:35,358
They can't be far then. Give me the keys

938
01:15:54,049 --> 01:15:55,175
Actually...

939
01:15:56,652 --> 01:16:00,679
I have something to confess

940
01:16:01,256 --> 01:16:02,086
What is it?

941
01:16:04,459 --> 01:16:07,189
I told you there was nothing
between Yeong-ae and me

942
01:16:09,865 --> 01:16:12,390
- We kissed
- What?

943
01:16:12,467 --> 01:16:16,597
But nothing else happened

944
01:16:17,072 --> 01:16:19,199
Don't you think it's strange?

945
01:16:19,274 --> 01:16:22,300
Why would she go out with you?

946
01:16:23,679 --> 01:16:27,706
I'm telling the truth
She kissed me first

947
01:16:32,187 --> 01:16:33,119
What's wrong?

948
01:16:34,489 --> 01:16:36,218
You don't believe me?

949
01:16:36,291 --> 01:16:39,818
It's not that...
I think she wanted money from you

950
01:16:39,895 --> 01:16:41,419
I think so too

951
01:16:42,698 --> 01:16:45,132
She kissed me to ask me for money?

952
01:16:45,200 --> 01:16:48,328
And she asked you to protect her

953
01:16:48,403 --> 01:16:50,633
She just wanted money,

954
01:16:50,706 --> 01:16:53,641
but guys could get the wrong idea

955
01:16:55,811 --> 01:16:58,939
She didn't say anything about money

956
01:16:59,014 --> 01:17:01,346
You didn't give her the chance,

957
01:17:01,416 --> 01:17:03,043
or she missed the right timing

958
01:17:04,419 --> 01:17:05,351
Timing?

959
01:17:10,726 --> 01:17:11,658
See you tomorrow!

960
01:17:14,730 --> 01:17:17,665
Forget it, I got tricked

961
01:17:19,034 --> 01:17:20,467
She wasn't all that
great anyway

962
01:17:20,535 --> 01:17:24,164
She wasn't? She was great
when you kissed her

963
01:17:24,239 --> 01:17:25,968
But now she's not all that

964
01:17:26,041 --> 01:17:29,169
- That's not what I said
- Do you regret it now?

965
01:17:29,244 --> 01:17:33,078
I don't regret it. I've got
nothing to do with her

966
01:17:33,148 --> 01:17:34,274
What about you?

967
01:17:35,751 --> 01:17:36,979
Your friend begged you for money

968
01:17:37,052 --> 01:17:40,078
but you refused... do you regret that?

969
01:17:40,155 --> 01:17:43,886
No, I could've been nicer

970
01:17:43,959 --> 01:17:47,690
but it was the right thing
to do in my situation

971
01:17:48,363 --> 01:17:49,887
I regret it

972
01:17:51,266 --> 01:17:54,702
I took photos secretly and
never spoke to her

973
01:17:55,470 --> 01:18:00,498
I don't know what she was like,
what problems she faced

974
01:18:01,376 --> 01:18:06,006
If I'd been brave enough to tell
her how pretty she was...

975
01:18:06,782 --> 01:18:10,513
Or tell her how much I liked her

976
01:18:12,988 --> 01:18:14,717
It's not really that difficult

977
01:18:17,492 --> 01:18:18,720
Of course...

978
01:18:18,794 --> 01:18:21,820
It's unfortunate that she
met men for their money

979
01:18:22,798 --> 01:18:26,734
But she did that to
chase her dream

980
01:18:28,804 --> 01:18:33,537
At least she had
a dream for herself

981
01:18:34,609 --> 01:18:35,541
Me...?

982
01:18:37,612 --> 01:18:41,343
I just did as I was told,

983
01:18:41,416 --> 01:18:43,441
I didn't know what I really wanted

984
01:18:44,019 --> 01:18:47,955
I never thought about it

985
01:18:52,928 --> 01:18:54,452
I regret that

986
01:18:56,031 --> 01:19:02,061
I only thought about money...
not about my dreams

987
01:19:02,838 --> 01:19:06,467
I'm the worst here

988
01:19:08,243 --> 01:19:09,870
I never thought about anything...

989
01:19:12,047 --> 01:19:13,776
I just wasted time

990
01:19:13,849 --> 01:19:15,077
It's sad

991
01:19:16,051 --> 01:19:21,284
We didn't kill her but we didn't
help save her either

992
01:19:42,577 --> 01:19:44,807
We should do something

993
01:19:44,880 --> 01:19:47,815
Let's meet that man
He's the one responsible

994
01:19:47,883 --> 01:19:50,010
He's not like that
He wouldn't kill someone

995
01:19:50,085 --> 01:19:51,814
He told the police where we were

996
01:19:51,887 --> 01:19:52,911
You don't know that.

997
01:19:52,988 --> 01:19:56,014
They could have tracked our cell phones

998
01:19:56,091 --> 01:19:59,117
It happened twice You called
him this morning too

999
01:19:59,194 --> 01:20:00,525
It's just co-incidence

1000
01:20:00,595 --> 01:20:03,223
It isn't a co-incidence
Don't you get it?

1001
01:20:03,298 --> 01:20:06,324
- Don't get so worked up
- Aren't you mad?

1002
01:20:06,401 --> 01:20:08,631
He's a dirty man playing
around with a young girl

1003
01:20:08,703 --> 01:20:11,433
- You can't prove that
- Didn't you see the photos?

1004
01:20:11,506 --> 01:20:14,031
We know he threatened Yeong-ae

1005
01:20:14,109 --> 01:20:16,043
He's capable of killing her

1006
01:20:16,111 --> 01:20:19,945
My boss wouldn't kill anyone

1007
01:20:20,015 --> 01:20:23,348
He's never acted strange
around her Not even once

1008
01:20:27,322 --> 01:20:28,846
You're here.

1009
01:20:28,924 --> 01:20:31,256
Could you help
Yeong-ae clean up?

1010
01:20:31,326 --> 01:20:34,261
Yeong-ae...
Take this with you

1011
01:20:39,134 --> 01:20:42,262
Yeong-ae was
usually so bright

1012
01:20:43,538 --> 01:20:48,669
But...she looked
so sad that day

1013
01:20:48,743 --> 01:20:50,176
It must be him

1014
01:20:50,245 --> 01:20:54,181
The police might be waiting there

1015
01:20:54,249 --> 01:20:56,376
If we get caught again

1016
01:20:56,451 --> 01:20:58,282
We have to tell them the truth

1017
01:20:58,954 --> 01:21:02,185
They didn't believe us when
we tried to tell them before

1018
01:21:21,776 --> 01:21:23,107
Stop right there

1019
01:21:25,180 --> 01:21:27,205
There's nowhere for you to run

1020
01:21:41,596 --> 01:21:42,426
Stop!

1021
01:21:43,198 --> 01:21:44,927
Don't come any closer, we'll jump

1022
01:21:45,000 --> 01:21:46,331
We mean it, we'll jump

1023
01:21:46,401 --> 01:21:47,925
You don't want us to die, do you?

1024
01:21:48,003 --> 01:21:50,631
Come over here, don't be silly

1025
01:21:50,705 --> 01:21:52,229
Jump if you're game enough

1026
01:21:53,508 --> 01:21:54,440
Don't say that

1027
01:21:54,509 --> 01:21:56,033
Did you hear what he said?

1028
01:21:56,111 --> 01:21:58,045
He was rude from the moment we met

1029
01:21:58,113 --> 01:22:01,139
- Don't think we won't jump!
- Fine, we'll wait

1030
01:22:01,216 --> 01:22:02,649
Don't take too long to decide

1031
01:22:03,818 --> 01:22:05,547
What if they really jump...

1032
01:22:05,620 --> 01:22:07,144
Trust me, they won't

1033
01:22:10,325 --> 01:22:12,452
- I think I can jump
- What?

1034
01:22:13,828 --> 01:22:16,763
- You mean it?
- Why not? we're 19

1035
01:22:17,632 --> 01:22:19,463
I'm game enough

1036
01:22:25,540 --> 01:22:27,770
I don't think they're joking

1037
01:22:27,842 --> 01:22:29,366
Don't fall for their tricks

1038
01:22:30,845 --> 01:22:32,073
Are you going to take responsibility?

1039
01:22:32,147 --> 01:22:33,774
Sure, I'll take the blame

1040
01:22:33,848 --> 01:22:36,078
We'll be together, even in heaven

1041
01:22:36,151 --> 01:22:38,676
I don't want to get fired

1042
01:22:38,753 --> 01:22:40,983
Go on, jump. Do it.

1043
01:22:56,271 --> 01:22:57,795
Wait, don't!

1044
01:22:58,473 --> 01:23:00,805
We'll let you go. We'll let you go

1045
01:23:00,875 --> 01:23:02,399
We're not letting them go

1046
01:23:16,891 --> 01:23:20,122
- They left the keys in the car
- Do you have a license?

1047
01:23:20,695 --> 01:23:23,721
You can acquire a license
when you're 18 but...

1048
01:23:23,798 --> 01:23:27,029
You still need parent
permission to buy a car

1049
01:23:27,802 --> 01:23:30,134
We can vote for a member of parliament

1050
01:23:30,205 --> 01:23:31,433
but we can't vote against policies

1051
01:23:31,506 --> 01:23:34,634
We're adults but still children
What do people want from us?

1052
01:23:50,125 --> 01:23:52,559
This is all for your own good

1053
01:23:59,834 --> 01:24:02,268
You know I'm on your side, right?

1054
01:24:24,459 --> 01:24:25,790
Welcome

1055
01:24:27,262 --> 01:24:30,197
- Is the boss in?
- He's gone out

1056
01:24:37,872 --> 01:24:38,896
Follow me

1057
01:24:51,986 --> 01:24:53,112
Hello

1058
01:24:54,189 --> 01:24:56,919
What are you doing here?

1059
01:24:56,991 --> 01:24:59,118
I thought you were
in Gangwon province

1060
01:24:59,894 --> 01:25:01,225
Did you come on your own?

1061
01:25:02,297 --> 01:25:03,229
Yeong-ae...

1062
01:25:05,200 --> 01:25:06,132
What?

1063
01:25:07,001 --> 01:25:10,437
Did you really go out with her?

1064
01:25:10,505 --> 01:25:12,336
What are you talking about?

1065
01:25:12,407 --> 01:25:16,138
Yeong-ae told me
she was seeing a man

1066
01:25:17,412 --> 01:25:20,745
I don't believe this
Why do you think it's me?

1067
01:25:20,815 --> 01:25:22,840
She said he was married

1068
01:25:22,917 --> 01:25:25,852
Am I the only married man?
